race.comment: EVAREADYMISS (8) is a promising galloper who is unbeaten from two runs, the latest success coming over 1000m at Townsville. Kept fresh for this and Lang sticks and will position on speed from an inside gate. Looks the testing material again. MISS LEANA (6) ran below expectations at Ipswich last time after being in contention on the turn. Comes back in grade and draws inside today. Finds a suitable race and can turn things around. SECRET CYPHER (7) finished midfield resuming from a break over 1200m at Doomben. He's switch to the gun Gollan yard and will be better for that run. One of the leading contenders. EKHIDNA (5) was beaten just 2L at Doomben and it was a big effort from the back. Draws well here and he she has plenty of scope for improvement. MISHANI BREEZE (11) had been racing well in the country in lesser grade but didn't fire 6 days ago at Murwillumbah. Tumbles 6kg in weight for this and can be running into it late at a price.
